<p>I'm using tooltips for a button and it's menu items but I'm having a problem where the tooltips are covering the buttons themselves and frustrating users.  I would like to position the tooltip completely to the left side of the button and menu items so that it does not cover any part of the element.  Is there a way to do this?</p>  <p>Example here: <a href="http://jsfiddle.net/0gv1er5v/" rel="nofollow">fiddle</a></p>  <pre><code>Ext.onReady(function () {      Ext.QuickTips.init();      Ext.create('Ext.container.Viewport', {         layout: 'fit',         padding: 100,         items: [{             tbar: {                 items: ['-&gt;',{                     text: 'Toolbar button',                     tooltip: 'toolbar button tooltip',                     menu: {                         items: [{                             tooltip: 'menu item tooltip',                             text: 'menu item'                         }]                     }                 }]             }         }]     }); }); </code></pre>